WEBVTT

00:03.337 --> 00:05.704
          [eerie music]

00:05.705 --> 00:09.041
      [footsteps clacking]

00:25.259 --> 00:30.229
  [playing "Goldberg Variations
  Aria" by J.S. Bach on piano]

01:01.562 --> 01:03.796
            [sighing]

01:05.099 --> 01:05.864
        [lighter flicks]

01:05.866 --> 01:09.301
           [breathing]

01:26.487 --> 01:31.423
    [record playing "Goldberg
 Variations Aria" by J.S. Bach]

01:42.570 --> 01:45.904
   [Leo] <i> There are five laws</i>
      <i> to create something</i>
         <i> from nothing.</i>

01:45.906 --> 01:47.739
          -[Lex] One.
    -[Leo] <i> Distribute being</i> .

01:47.741 --> 01:49.708
       <i> A single honeybee</i>
   <i> has a memory of six days,</i>

01:49.710 --> 01:51.910
<i>a hive a memory of three months.</i>

01:53.114 --> 01:54.346
           [Lex] Two.

01:54.348 --> 01:56.381
   [Leo] <i> Accept your errors.</i>

01:56.383 --> 01:58.717
         <i> Innovation is</i>
<i>indistinguishable from failing.</i>

02:00.654 --> 02:04.656
         -[Lex] Three.
 -[Leo] <i> Inherit the wind. Cause</i>
    <i> unrest and invite chaos.</i>

02:06.594 --> 02:09.127
          -[Lex] Four.
        -[Leo] <i> Sacrifice</i>
       <i> form for function.</i>

02:10.497 --> 02:12.297
  <i> If it works, it's beautiful.</i>

02:19.507 --> 02:21.840
             -Five.
          -[Leo] <i> Yield</i>
      <i> increasing returns.</i>

02:21.842 --> 02:23.842
       <i> To those who have,</i>
      <i> more will be given.</i>

02:23.844 --> 02:26.445
          [Lex laughs]

02:33.220 --> 02:35.154
         [ice rattling]

02:35.156 --> 02:38.423
      [electronic whirring]

02:44.765 --> 02:45.898
              What?

02:50.471 --> 02:52.638
            [buzzing]

02:54.842 --> 02:59.945
 ["Well-Tempered Clavier: Fugue
  #2 in C Minor" by J.S. Bach]

03:44.024 --> 03:47.426
 -[Leo] I love your [indistinct]
          [Lex] Thanks.

03:47.428 --> 03:48.660
         Happy birthday.

03:48.662 --> 03:50.362
          [Lex laughs]

03:50.364 --> 03:52.965
         [Leo whispers]

03:54.368 --> 03:56.902
          [Leo shushes]

04:03.644 --> 04:05.611
      Don't we look alike?

04:10.718 --> 04:11.917
            My room.

04:11.919 --> 04:15.554
         [creepy music]

04:15.556 --> 04:18.589
        [static buzzing]

04:19.593 --> 04:20.559
            Bathroom.

04:22.730 --> 04:23.829
        And drum roll...

04:26.500 --> 04:27.566
           Spare room.

04:27.568 --> 04:30.369
         [ominous music]

04:36.610 --> 04:37.976
      [speaking in French]

04:51.525 --> 04:54.793
       [Dru] Your brother
    is not fond of strangers.

04:54.795 --> 04:57.596
          [tense music]

05:01.669 --> 05:03.602
         You didn't tell
      me you were adopted.

05:05.572 --> 05:07.706
    They found me in a basket
        among the reeds.

05:10.844 --> 05:11.977
            And Leo?

05:13.881 --> 05:14.946
            [Lex] Hm.

05:14.948 --> 05:16.048
          In a handbag.

05:17.351 --> 05:19.484
      In Victoria Station.

05:19.486 --> 05:20.652
           [Dru] Okay.

05:22.489 --> 05:23.855
         What else am I
     gonna learn this week?

05:28.028 --> 05:29.027
         I took a test.

05:29.029 --> 05:31.730
          [tense music]

05:34.601 --> 05:35.801
          I'm pregnant.

05:44.745 --> 05:45.877
           It's true.

05:49.483 --> 05:50.449
           Seriously.

05:51.719 --> 05:53.385
        Are you serious?

05:56.657 --> 05:57.589
          -Don't do it.
            -[laughs]

05:57.591 --> 05:59.624
          [both laugh]

05:59.626 --> 06:01.059
     Why would you do that?

06:01.061 --> 06:02.427
     Why would you do that?

06:02.429 --> 06:04.863
            -You f--
          -[Lex laughs]

06:07.668 --> 06:09.935
           [clicking]

06:09.937 --> 06:11.503
            [typing]

06:11.505 --> 06:14.473
         [spooky music]

06:16.777 --> 06:20.912
           [moves into
    upbeat electronic music]

06:22.783 --> 06:25.050
            [beeping]

06:26.820 --> 06:29.988
      [electronic buzzing]

07:14.067 --> 07:17.936
[people applauding and cheering]

07:20.073 --> 07:22.007
        Does anyone ever
      feel the same emotion

07:22.009 --> 07:24.910
   for a butterfly or a flower

07:25.946 --> 07:27.746
 that they feel for a cathedral?

07:28.582 --> 07:31.550
        [people laughing]

07:32.186 --> 07:33.185
        [teeth snapping]

07:33.187 --> 07:34.519
          Or a picture?

07:36.590 --> 07:38.824
        [glass clinking]

07:42.996 --> 07:44.463
     I know why you're here.

07:45.866 --> 07:46.998
          Bloodsuckers.

07:48.135 --> 07:51.269
         But I'm afraid
       I am to disappoint.

07:51.271 --> 07:54.906
       [electronic music]

07:55.943 --> 07:57.542
       [door slides open]

07:57.544 --> 07:58.577
              Lex?

07:59.913 --> 08:01.780
    Not this year, no tricks.

08:01.782 --> 08:03.915
       No hacks, no bugs.

08:03.917 --> 08:05.750
         [solemn music]

08:09.289 --> 08:10.555
           What's up?

08:12.860 --> 08:14.559
    They're not his friends.

08:17.631 --> 08:18.864
           No, no, no.

08:18.866 --> 08:22.534
   This year we are the virus.

08:22.536 --> 08:23.869
         [ominous music]

08:44.691 --> 08:47.726
          [piano chord]

09:07.247 --> 09:08.313
              Lex?

09:13.086 --> 09:16.288
      [electronic whirring]

09:16.290 --> 09:19.624
      [veiled piano music]

10:11.878 --> 10:14.245
           [squishing]

10:36.203 --> 10:37.902
         [drain sucking]

10:41.942 --> 10:44.643
        [static buzzing]

10:44.645 --> 10:47.278
         [ghostly music]

11:07.734 --> 11:10.301
           [bubbling]

11:14.675 --> 11:16.007
            [clicks]

11:18.845 --> 11:21.046
   [Dru] What do you do, Leo?

11:21.048 --> 11:22.814
        Live and breathe.

11:22.816 --> 11:25.784
         I know, I know,
     call me old-fashioned,

11:25.786 --> 11:26.751
       but it's good work.

11:29.022 --> 11:30.955
  If you can get it, of course.

11:34.127 --> 11:36.361
       I answer questions.

11:37.431 --> 11:38.863
         I'm an artist.

11:38.865 --> 11:41.132
    Don't they ask questions,
        not answer them?

11:41.134 --> 11:44.402
       -Only the bad ones.
    -What is it you say, Dru?

11:44.404 --> 11:47.739
      Art allows us to find
  ourselves and lose ourselves?

11:47.741 --> 11:49.007
          It's a quote.

11:51.111 --> 11:52.210
           I am lost.

11:54.114 --> 11:55.080
           I am found.

11:57.217 --> 11:58.216
       Oh, I'm lost again.

12:10.230 --> 12:11.930
           [Leo hums]

12:27.981 --> 12:28.947
           Hey, smilo.

12:31.985 --> 12:32.951
        [cabinet creaks]

12:36.790 --> 12:37.856
         [cabinet thuds]

12:40.961 --> 12:43.795
       He that is jealous
         is not in love.

12:43.797 --> 12:46.297
          [eerie music]

12:50.370 --> 12:51.336
            Jealous?

12:55.776 --> 12:57.909
         Don't you mean,
     "I love you, darling."

13:00.347 --> 13:02.547
    We grew up together, Dru.

13:04.184 --> 13:05.917
   We didn't have anyone else.

13:10.023 --> 13:12.090
        [beads rattling]

13:18.431 --> 13:20.498
         [drain sucking]

13:25.539 --> 13:28.006
           [gurgling]

13:52.199 --> 13:53.298
           [squishing]

13:53.300 --> 13:55.633
           [dripping]

13:58.238 --> 14:01.539
     [haunting piano music]

14:08.481 --> 14:09.881
         [worm squeaks]

14:23.330 --> 14:25.396
   [Dru] It's been a pleasure.

14:25.398 --> 14:26.998
           Leo, mate.

14:34.541 --> 14:37.342
          Come on, Lex.
    Come on, please don't go.

14:37.344 --> 14:40.178
         [shadowy music]

14:57.063 --> 14:58.663
        Fuck, fuck, fuck!

14:58.665 --> 15:01.299
 The pleasure, it was all mine.

15:02.702 --> 15:04.068
           [Lex] Wait!

15:04.070 --> 15:06.037
           [clicking]

15:06.039 --> 15:08.606
       [suspenseful music]

15:10.076 --> 15:12.143
      [electronic whirring]

15:17.984 --> 15:18.950
              Easy.

15:18.952 --> 15:23.955
    [Dru] I'm not asking you
  to leave, okay. You can stay.

15:23.957 --> 15:27.191
   -But I've, I've had enough.
    -We've been here one day!

15:27.193 --> 15:30.628
   You know I haven't seen him
     in years! Please just,
 just stay a little bit longer!

15:32.399 --> 15:33.631
             Please.

15:34.668 --> 15:37.201
        [static buzzing]

15:37.203 --> 15:39.304
           [crackling]

15:39.306 --> 15:42.540
      [electronic rumbling]

15:44.711 --> 15:46.678
           [clicking]

15:46.680 --> 15:50.014
      [electronic humming]

15:57.057 --> 16:00.191
      Daisy sucked too much
  current and tripped the fuse.

16:00.193 --> 16:01.159
             Daisy?

16:01.962 --> 16:02.760
              Yes.

16:05.165 --> 16:07.031
    The system's fail-secure.

16:07.033 --> 16:09.300
       If the power cuts,
     the door stays locked.

16:18.211 --> 16:20.011
           [clicking]

16:24.117 --> 16:25.149
           Good luck.

16:26.219 --> 16:28.386
     [electronic crunching]

16:30.123 --> 16:31.055
             [beeps]

16:31.057 --> 16:32.156
           [Leo] Okay!

16:37.030 --> 16:40.365
        [static buzzing]

16:40.367 --> 16:44.168
           [clicking]

16:45.372 --> 16:46.671
     [Dru] What's the story?

16:47.807 --> 16:49.040
        [static buzzing]

16:49.042 --> 16:51.075
   [Leo] A system reset maybe.

16:51.077 --> 16:52.343
            [beeping]

16:52.345 --> 16:53.611
     [Dru] Still no signal.

16:54.581 --> 16:57.048
      [electronic whirring]

16:57.050 --> 16:59.217
         [somber music]

17:01.154 --> 17:02.387
    [Leo] What are you doing?

17:02.389 --> 17:05.022
    -Using Daisy's Internet.
          -It's ergot.

17:05.025 --> 17:06.491
         [Lex] English!

17:06.492 --> 17:07.692
        Not connected.

17:10.096 --> 17:11.662
        Security threat.

17:11.664 --> 17:12.630
               So?

17:14.567 --> 17:15.532
              What?

17:17.637 --> 17:20.304
            -We wait.
      -[Dru] Wait for what?

17:20.306 --> 17:22.640
        For me to regain
 access to the security module.

17:23.843 --> 17:25.376
   Or until someone drops by.

17:26.378 --> 17:28.679
           [gurgling]

17:30.050 --> 17:30.848
              Tea?

17:32.585 --> 17:34.052
    We can bang on the walls.

17:34.054 --> 17:35.420
   The neighbors will hear us.

17:35.422 --> 17:38.623
        [Leo] We are the
   only residents these days.

17:38.625 --> 17:40.158
    You've evicted everyone?

17:41.461 --> 17:42.427
              Leo?

17:42.429 --> 17:43.494
       I gave them notice.

17:44.397 --> 17:46.597
      [speaking in French]

17:46.599 --> 17:47.698
       Excuse her French.

17:50.303 --> 17:52.870
    You own the whole block?

17:52.872 --> 17:54.305
         Yeah, us both.

17:54.307 --> 17:55.673
        We inherited it.

17:58.344 --> 17:59.577
           [slurping]

18:01.448 --> 18:03.448
        [metal rattling]

18:03.450 --> 18:06.317
         [spooky music]

18:08.421 --> 18:09.420
              Keys.

18:10.523 --> 18:11.522
         [metal clanks]

18:12.859 --> 18:15.893
       [mysterious music]

18:41.821 --> 18:43.221
            [blowing]

18:44.858 --> 18:46.724
           [trickling]

18:49.229 --> 18:50.194
         [Lex] So what?

18:52.332 --> 18:53.698
         [Dru] We wait.

19:00.907 --> 19:02.473
   We'll ration our supplies.

19:04.144 --> 19:05.176
       She's got a point.

19:05.178 --> 19:07.745
     If we have to wait for
 one of your friends to drop by,

19:07.747 --> 19:09.447
  we could be here for a while.

19:14.654 --> 19:15.686
           No offense.

19:17.790 --> 19:21.893
  ["Goldberg Variations No 13"
    by Johann Sebastian Bach]

19:38.178 --> 19:39.610
               Mm!

19:39.612 --> 19:40.978
        [metal scraping]

19:45.952 --> 19:49.654
    [Leo] A priest, a rabbi,
  and an imam walk into a bar.

19:50.857 --> 19:52.924
           The barman
     looks at them and says,

19:52.926 --> 19:55.493
         "What is this,
       some kind of joke?"

19:55.495 --> 19:58.829
           -[Dru] Wow.
          -[Leo laughs]

19:59.799 --> 20:03.234
     [Leo] Come on. Come on.

20:09.375 --> 20:11.442
      She talks about you.

20:11.444 --> 20:12.610
          All the time.

20:22.589 --> 20:26.290
            ["Within"
     by Luke Marzec playing]

20:29.762 --> 20:31.762
              [Dru]
   Do you remember how we met?

20:36.302 --> 20:37.301
         You were alone.

20:39.038 --> 20:40.771
    I asked if you were okay.

20:40.773 --> 20:42.573
       And what did I say?

20:42.575 --> 20:44.875
  [Dru] Not a lot... at first.

20:46.713 --> 20:48.813
  You were dressed all in black
   even though it was so hot.

20:53.519 --> 20:55.586
    [Lex] I couldn't face it.

20:55.588 --> 20:56.654
          [bell gongs]

20:56.656 --> 20:58.489
       [Lex] The funeral.

20:58.491 --> 21:00.992
 [Dru] You didn't like your dad.

21:00.994 --> 21:02.793
 [Lex] We never really knew him.

21:04.731 --> 21:06.430
     He was always working,

21:06.432 --> 21:07.798
   even after we were adopted.

21:08.601 --> 21:11.402
         After mom died,
     he worked even harder.

21:11.404 --> 21:12.803
          [fly buzzing]

21:24.717 --> 21:26.417
   We had whatever we wanted.

21:28.321 --> 21:30.488
       An endless holiday,
       just the two of us.

21:32.292 --> 21:34.659
          In that house
     that was our universe.

21:34.661 --> 21:36.961
           [whirring]

21:41.968 --> 21:43.934
     But everyone grows up.

22:31.551 --> 22:34.585
       [slow piano music]

22:37.557 --> 22:39.690
           -[slicing]
              -Ow!

22:39.692 --> 22:42.793
          [piano music]

22:44.630 --> 22:46.964
           [clinking]

22:48.701 --> 22:50.701
       [Lex] New category.

22:50.703 --> 22:54.605
     Characters from fiction
     with the same initials.

22:56.142 --> 22:57.174
            Example.

22:59.879 --> 23:00.945
          Willy Wonka.

23:02.915 --> 23:05.883
           Rook to C4.

23:07.520 --> 23:08.786
          Mighty Mouse.

23:12.892 --> 23:18.162
     Uh... Bishop... to F7.

23:18.164 --> 23:19.397
              And?

23:20.600 --> 23:21.699
           Bugs Bunny.

23:21.701 --> 23:23.768
        The Great Gatsby.

23:23.770 --> 23:25.569
          Knight to D7.

23:25.571 --> 23:27.104
             Check.

23:27.106 --> 23:29.673
        Wait. Checkmate.

23:29.675 --> 23:31.609
        It's Jay Gatsby,
        not Great Gatsby,

23:31.611 --> 23:33.444
         and it's my go.

23:33.446 --> 23:34.979
           Peter Pan.

23:34.981 --> 23:35.946
          Peter Parker!

23:39.018 --> 23:41.719
      [electronic whirring]

23:47.126 --> 23:50.161
    Can you not cool her down
       a wee bit, captain?

23:52.565 --> 23:56.033
             It's an
   inanimate object, firstly,

23:56.035 --> 23:58.002
        and no, I can't.

23:58.871 --> 24:00.538
      The fans are damaged.

24:00.540 --> 24:03.641
    You two had an argument?

24:07.447 --> 24:08.913
    You don't have to answer.

24:16.522 --> 24:18.522
     Daisy is not hardware.

24:18.524 --> 24:19.523
         She's a virus.

24:22.094 --> 24:23.060
           [Lex] Look.

24:30.770 --> 24:31.802
           That's new.

24:39.178 --> 24:41.011
     There are five laws to
 create something from nothing.

24:41.013 --> 24:44.782
        D-A-I-S-Y. Daisy.

24:44.784 --> 24:47.818
        And these are the
     laws your virus obeys?

24:47.820 --> 24:49.487
 [Leo] These laws must be obeyed

24:49.489 --> 24:51.889
        by anything that
       wishes to survive.

24:51.891 --> 24:53.557
         [chaotic music]

24:59.565 --> 25:01.565
   [Leo] D, distribute being.

25:02.835 --> 25:05.836
    The whole is worth more
   than the sum of its parts.

25:06.639 --> 25:09.273
        A single honeybee
    has a memory of six days,

25:09.275 --> 25:13.310
        the hive a memory
        of three months.

25:15.281 --> 25:16.580
    [Dru] And the second law?

25:16.582 --> 25:17.948
    [Leo] Accept your errors.

25:19.519 --> 25:21.886
          Innovation is
 indistinguishable from failure.

25:22.755 --> 25:26.290
  To be an error and to be cast
  out is part of God's design.

25:27.960 --> 25:29.126
            [Lex] I?

25:29.128 --> 25:30.561
     [Leo] Inherit the wind.

25:31.264 --> 25:33.330
 Cause unrest and invite chaos.

25:38.204 --> 25:39.703
        [Dru] And the S?

25:39.705 --> 25:41.906
      [Leo] Sacrifice form
          for function.

25:41.908 --> 25:43.173
         Fuck elegance.

25:43.175 --> 25:45.075
  If it works, it's beautiful.

25:45.077 --> 25:48.178
               -Y?
   -Yield increasing returns.

25:48.180 --> 25:50.180
       Nurture successes.

25:50.182 --> 25:52.182
       -[tires squealing]
          -[indistinct]

25:52.184 --> 25:54.852
        -[metal crashing]
        -[water gushing]

26:00.660 --> 26:01.992
    Survival of the fittest.

26:05.298 --> 26:08.632
       -What's the threat?
            -She is.

26:08.634 --> 26:11.602
Her weakest traits she destroys.

26:12.371 --> 26:13.871
      Artificial selection.

26:14.740 --> 26:16.340
  Judge, jury, and executioner.

26:16.342 --> 26:17.708
       And the defendant.

26:20.813 --> 26:21.879
        What's the point?

26:22.815 --> 26:24.181
         Understanding.

26:26.385 --> 26:27.918
    She's learning to learn.

26:30.590 --> 26:31.989
          [door slams]

26:31.991 --> 26:35.092
        [insects buzzing]

26:44.737 --> 26:47.171
      [buzzing intensifies]

26:50.810 --> 26:52.610
        [water splashing]

26:54.981 --> 26:55.946
        [glass shatters]

26:58.684 --> 27:00.017
              Wait.

27:00.019 --> 27:02.886
        [troubled music]

27:06.425 --> 27:08.292
         [Lex] Leo, Leo!

27:10.730 --> 27:12.129
          [Lex screams]

27:12.131 --> 27:14.698
     Get it out, get it out!
           Get it out!

27:14.700 --> 27:16.834
           [spraying]

27:21.107 --> 27:24.441
      [electronic whirring]

27:30.116 --> 27:31.415
          [door creaks]

27:31.417 --> 27:32.383
           [Lex] Leo!

27:33.686 --> 27:34.785
              Leo!

27:38.724 --> 27:40.891
           [Leo gasps]

27:40.893 --> 27:41.859
         [Lex] Oh shit.

27:42.862 --> 27:45.963
       [slow piano music]

27:55.074 --> 27:57.441
           [crackling]

28:26.172 --> 28:28.806
          -[Leo gasps]
            -Shhhh...

28:44.790 --> 28:46.190
           [Lex] Well?

28:46.192 --> 28:48.292
      -[Leo] I don't know.
        -Don't know what?

28:48.294 --> 28:50.794
      What are you asking?

28:50.796 --> 28:52.096
          I don't know.

29:01.373 --> 29:04.241
           [gurgling]

29:06.145 --> 29:07.811
         [ice rattling]

29:07.813 --> 29:09.079
        [beads rattling]

29:19.992 --> 29:21.425
  You don't know what they are?

29:24.130 --> 29:25.829
            They have
     nothing to do with you?

29:30.102 --> 29:31.068
        How's your head?

29:41.981 --> 29:43.180
      What are we gonna do?

29:51.157 --> 29:54.024
      [electronic whirring]

29:54.026 --> 29:58.495
      ["Say One More Time"
     by Luke Marzec playing]

30:01.100 --> 30:03.233
 [Leo] When I was a young child,

30:03.235 --> 30:06.370
 I performed open-heart surgery
     on the neighbor's cat.

30:10.009 --> 30:11.875
   While our father was away,

30:12.511 --> 30:17.281
  I found all the papers, cash,
checkbooks, and credit cards,

30:18.317 --> 30:20.017
        and burned them.

30:23.923 --> 30:28.025
   This bottle of whiskey that
  we've all been drinking from

30:28.961 --> 30:32.229
        is spiked with a
   very powerful and very rare

30:32.231 --> 30:34.198
       slow-acting poison.

30:36.335 --> 30:37.568
     Which of these is true?

30:39.371 --> 30:40.337
           None of it.

30:41.640 --> 30:43.106
           Very good.

30:43.108 --> 30:44.308
        How did you know?

30:48.614 --> 30:51.348
  The cat was in fact a mouse.

30:51.350 --> 30:57.354
   Lex burned daddy's papers,
     with my help naturally,
     though it was her idea.

30:57.356 --> 31:00.457
         And no, I'm not
   checking us all out early,

31:00.459 --> 31:02.259
       although I did pick
     this up on my travels,

31:02.261 --> 31:05.996
      and I did think today
    was as good a day as any.

31:05.998 --> 31:06.997
           To family.

31:08.100 --> 31:09.299
        [Dru] To family.

31:09.301 --> 31:11.935
            [laughs]

31:17.977 --> 31:20.210
     Do you believe in God?

31:30.122 --> 31:33.523
          You're asking
  whether I believe, like Lex,

31:33.525 --> 31:36.393
      that in another life
   we'll see our mother again?

31:38.464 --> 31:41.164
            -Do you?
              -No.

31:41.166 --> 31:42.900
          -About which?
          -None of it.

31:42.902 --> 31:44.034
     How can you be certain?

31:45.638 --> 31:51.208
   Let me ask you a question.
          You're smart.

31:51.210 --> 31:52.242
           Thank you.

31:55.714 --> 31:59.049
     You could do anything,

31:59.051 --> 32:00.384
        yet here you are,

32:01.620 --> 32:03.086
          playing chess

32:04.556 --> 32:06.556
   against your own computer.

32:06.558 --> 32:09.259
        And here you are,
     a drunk sack of carbon

32:09.261 --> 32:11.261
heckling another sack of carbon.

32:11.263 --> 32:13.430
        Ignore him, Dru.
    He's a bitter little boy

32:13.432 --> 32:14.998
          with thoughts
      too big for his head.

32:15.000 --> 32:16.400
               Ah.

32:16.402 --> 32:18.735
        What book did you
     parrot that from, sis?

32:20.339 --> 32:23.373
Do you actually have any friends
      or just acquaintances
    you bribe with software?

32:23.375 --> 32:24.341
          [Dru snorts]

32:27.313 --> 32:31.248
       Because the company
    you keep is so charming.

32:36.655 --> 32:38.956
   <i> ¶ When all is ending now ¶</i>

32:38.958 --> 32:42.659
       <i> ¶ I don't know if</i>
      <i> I'll ever carry on ¶</i>

32:42.661 --> 32:44.561
What if someone buzzes the door?

32:46.598 --> 32:48.098
     We mustn't fall asleep.

32:54.740 --> 32:55.739
      [laughs] We mustn't.

32:58.477 --> 32:59.443
             Please.

33:08.554 --> 33:11.288
            -[coughs]
            -[laughs]

33:14.059 --> 33:17.027
        [static buzzing]

33:25.604 --> 33:28.338
         [veiled music]

33:50.129 --> 33:52.429
           [jingling]

33:56.135 --> 33:57.100
            [gagging]

33:57.102 --> 34:00.270
      [electronic humming]

34:19.190 --> 34:21.625
            [coughs]

34:23.228 --> 34:25.829
           -[retching]
         -[splattering]

34:39.578 --> 34:41.378
              [Leo]
 They all have the same texture.

34:42.380 --> 34:43.346
            Fractal.

34:44.583 --> 34:46.449
        The same pattern
     repeated over and over.

34:47.286 --> 34:49.453
       The surface area to
   volume ratio must be huge,

34:49.455 --> 34:51.888
       giving them maximum
  exposure to the environment.

34:53.492 --> 34:54.458
            But why?

34:56.360 --> 34:58.595
-[Dru] Where did they come from?
  -Heightened sensory awareness

34:58.597 --> 35:00.230
 for increased heat absorption.

35:00.232 --> 35:01.565
    [Lex] You look terrible.

35:02.534 --> 35:04.501
         [drain sucking]

35:05.504 --> 35:06.703
           [Leo gasps]

35:06.705 --> 35:08.672
            [zapping]

35:08.674 --> 35:11.274
         It's generating
      its own electricity.

35:14.446 --> 35:17.280
         [ominous music]

35:28.794 --> 35:31.528
     [Leo] The organisms are
       copied from nature.

35:31.530 --> 35:33.663
          I say copied.
    She's borrowed liberally.

35:36.635 --> 35:39.236
         She's reforming
     the matter into tissue.

35:39.238 --> 35:42.672
          The maggots,
    the insects, that plant.

35:44.276 --> 35:45.942
      They're part of her.

35:47.679 --> 35:50.313
  She's harvesting information.

35:53.352 --> 35:56.419
    [Leo] No, no, no, no, no!
       What are you doing!
      Stop, stop, stop it!

35:56.421 --> 35:57.687
    [Lex] What are you doing!

35:57.689 --> 35:59.156
      [electronic buzzing]

35:59.158 --> 36:00.190
              -Dru!
            -Stop it!

36:01.226 --> 36:02.392
           [Lex] Leo!

36:03.595 --> 36:06.196
          [Leo shouts]

36:07.466 --> 36:10.200
        [heavy breathing]

36:10.202 --> 36:12.869
      [electronic humming]

36:18.677 --> 36:20.977
           [dripping]

36:23.215 --> 36:25.749
           [rumbling]

36:29.288 --> 36:32.255
        [wobbly whirring]

36:45.470 --> 36:47.771
    [Leo] Oh, that's my girl.

36:49.374 --> 36:52.609
      [electronic whirring]

36:55.714 --> 36:57.948
          [Leo laughs]

37:01.019 --> 37:04.221
       [foreboding music]

37:13.966 --> 37:16.566
     [Leo gasps and coughs]

37:20.672 --> 37:22.272
              Wait!

37:22.274 --> 37:23.940
      Lex! Get out the way!

37:29.281 --> 37:30.247
             Think.

37:31.583 --> 37:32.649
    Think what it did to you.

37:32.651 --> 37:33.683
          She's right.

37:40.459 --> 37:41.858
       It's too dangerous.

38:00.646 --> 38:04.981
       -[insects buzzing]
           -[hissing]

38:16.962 --> 38:18.795
           [squeaking]

38:18.797 --> 38:21.698
       [electric buzzing]

38:24.369 --> 38:26.469
     [Leo] New recruits were
     always given buzz cuts
    at the start of training,

38:26.471 --> 38:28.571
          initially to
   prevent the spread of lice.

38:29.675 --> 38:31.374
         Over time this
     developed into uniform

38:31.376 --> 38:33.877
      under the pretext of
  easy maintenance and cooling.

38:35.681 --> 38:37.747
 In reality it was another tool

38:37.749 --> 38:40.950
        in the attempt to
  depersonalize the individual.

38:40.952 --> 38:42.585
        Comrades looking
     into each other's eyes

38:42.587 --> 38:44.020
            would see
   themselves reflected back,

38:44.022 --> 38:46.589
        inspiring empathy
   with their fellow soldiers.

38:52.664 --> 38:55.131
       [foreboding music]

38:55.133 --> 38:56.132
             Unity.

38:56.134 --> 38:58.368
           Allegiance.

38:58.370 --> 39:00.437
  Worker bees and soldier ants.

39:00.439 --> 39:02.706
      Long live the queen!

39:06.144 --> 39:07.077
     [Dru] Look for signal.

39:07.079 --> 39:08.044
          [Lex] We did.

39:08.046 --> 39:09.546
           Look again.

39:18.957 --> 39:20.957
    [Leo] Hey. Whatcha doing?

39:23.095 --> 39:25.428
    [Leo] What are you doing?

39:25.430 --> 39:28.531
           Uh, you're
     looking for an escape?

39:30.936 --> 39:32.802
  [Dru] What's your suggestion?

39:32.804 --> 39:36.106
         My suggestion?

39:36.108 --> 39:38.041
          I don't know.

39:38.043 --> 39:39.476
 I'm just starting to have fun.

39:41.513 --> 39:43.079
       My headache's gone.

39:43.081 --> 39:45.782
        I feel cleansed.

39:46.852 --> 39:48.051
           Oi, Santa!

39:54.025 --> 39:55.125
              Hey!

40:04.002 --> 40:05.068
           Seriously?

40:08.106 --> 40:09.672
            [tapping]

40:09.674 --> 40:11.174
        What do you say?

40:12.010 --> 40:14.778
  Brother-in-law bonding sesh?

40:16.415 --> 40:18.014
    I'll go easy, I promise.

40:20.118 --> 40:21.718
         You like games?

40:25.457 --> 40:28.625
      [electronic buzzing]

40:30.529 --> 40:33.129
            [beeping]

40:36.902 --> 40:37.867
             Cheers.

40:43.442 --> 40:44.641
  How long have you lived here?

40:49.981 --> 40:52.949
           -How long?
             -Years.

40:52.951 --> 40:55.552
      -So, long enough to--
           -Your move.

40:58.824 --> 41:01.057
         -To know any--
      -Any secret passages,

41:01.059 --> 41:02.792
           wormholes.

41:02.794 --> 41:03.827
        Yeah, presumably.

41:04.863 --> 41:06.095
      No phone connection.

41:07.165 --> 41:09.966
   No Internet. No neighbors.

41:11.470 --> 41:13.837
   Electronic locking system.

41:13.839 --> 41:15.605
       Shuttered windows.

41:16.975 --> 41:18.675
        [Leo] Checkmate.

41:19.978 --> 41:22.278
          The shutters,
       where are the keys?

41:26.251 --> 41:27.217
          [Leo] Again.

41:30.088 --> 41:31.054
            The keys?

41:32.157 --> 41:33.490
              Left.

41:33.492 --> 41:34.924
 The white's in your left hand.

41:38.663 --> 41:40.296
       Micro expressions.

41:40.298 --> 41:42.765
    Well, macro in your case.

41:42.767 --> 41:45.301
      The way you held out
     your hands, your eyes.

41:47.072 --> 41:49.572
     How can you know this?

41:49.574 --> 41:51.307
    Because Daisy knows this.

41:53.778 --> 41:56.045
            [beeping]

42:02.020 --> 42:04.587
   Come on, come on, come on.

42:05.957 --> 42:08.758
         [phone ringing]

42:15.233 --> 42:18.234
        [static buzzing]

42:18.236 --> 42:21.571
      Hello? I'm locked in
      an apartment on um--

42:21.573 --> 42:24.207
          [dispatcher]
  <i> Emergency services have been</i>
     <i> temporarily suspended</i>

42:24.209 --> 42:26.976
  <i> in the Greater London Area.</i>

42:26.978 --> 42:29.012
 <i> In case of a structural fire,</i>

42:29.014 --> 42:32.015
     <i> evacuate the premises</i>
 <i> immediately please. Thank you.</i>

42:32.017 --> 42:34.117
            [beeping]

42:50.235 --> 42:53.236
            [groans]

42:56.374 --> 42:58.207
            [beeping]

43:18.096 --> 43:20.697
        [static buzzing]

43:47.325 --> 43:49.292
          [clattering]

43:53.331 --> 43:54.397
   <i> You've been recording us.</i>

43:55.767 --> 43:57.133
    You've been recording us.

43:58.236 --> 43:59.702
        This whole time.

44:00.805 --> 44:01.938
           Recording?

44:01.940 --> 44:02.905
               No.

44:04.743 --> 44:07.977
      I fed Daisy the video
      as initial stimulus!

44:07.979 --> 44:11.147
     It's been watching us.

44:11.149 --> 44:13.049
        [clattering]

44:13.051 --> 44:14.350
              -Lex!
             -What?

44:14.352 --> 44:15.385
       It's too dangerous.

44:16.688 --> 44:19.022
        It's not him,
  all right, it's the computer.

44:19.024 --> 44:20.723
   So you're on his side now?

44:20.725 --> 44:24.394
   Listen to me, I think it's
     gone to his head. Lex!

44:27.899 --> 44:28.865
          [lock clicks]

44:34.706 --> 44:35.805
       Turn the light off.

44:37.809 --> 44:38.775
             [click]

44:51.322 --> 44:52.355
           Stay there.

44:55.460 --> 44:58.261
  Right, so you can see me here
     and me on the monitors.

44:58.263 --> 44:59.729
           [Dru] Yeah.

45:19.851 --> 45:21.818
       What, what is this?

45:21.820 --> 45:23.219
       Their predictions.

45:23.221 --> 45:25.888
So what, it can tell the future?

45:25.890 --> 45:28.491
          She's making
      very educated guesses

45:28.493 --> 45:30.993
          based on her
  observation of our behavior.

45:44.509 --> 45:48.111
     When I look at myself,
      the image disappears.

45:49.247 --> 45:50.213
            Feedback.

45:50.215 --> 45:54.884
  Seeing yourself in the future
 influences you in the present.

45:56.121 --> 45:58.888
         Choice. Try it.

45:58.890 --> 46:00.490
      What do I have to do?

46:01.326 --> 46:03.025
       Whatever you want.

46:25.550 --> 46:29.185
         [ominous music]

46:39.597 --> 46:42.064
           [dripping]

47:10.061 --> 47:11.594
           [cork pops]

47:24.943 --> 47:26.242
           [knocking]

47:28.413 --> 47:31.480
     -[door handle rattling]
        -[liquid hissing]

47:31.482 --> 47:33.649
  [Dru] I know you're in there.

47:35.520 --> 47:37.954
           [bubbling]

47:37.956 --> 47:39.856
      Just gonna wait here.

47:53.071 --> 47:54.036
              Lex?

47:58.576 --> 47:59.609
           I love you.

48:01.212 --> 48:05.248
     I uh... don't say that

48:06.985 --> 48:08.017
           very often.

48:20.698 --> 48:23.599
     Please, open the door.

48:33.077 --> 48:35.611
          [Leo humming]

48:39.918 --> 48:42.285
     <i> ¶ I will not forget ¶</i>

48:42.287 --> 48:44.320
 <i> ¶ The day when we first met ¶</i>

48:44.322 --> 48:46.322
   <i> ¶ You were so beautiful ¶</i>

48:46.324 --> 48:49.358
  <i> ¶ I couldn't trust my eyes ¶</i>

48:49.360 --> 48:52.328
           <i> ¶ You were</i>
     <i> Dancing on the floor ¶</i>

48:52.330 --> 48:55.331
  <i> ¶ I was in a state of awe ¶</i>

48:55.333 --> 49:00.202
       <i> ¶ Imagining myself</i>
      <i> Right by your side ¶</i>

49:00.204 --> 49:02.738
 <i> ¶ So I asked you for a dance ¶</i>

49:02.740 --> 49:06.142
<i>¶ You said okay but no thanks ¶</i>

49:06.144 --> 49:10.713
        <i> ¶ I've got a guy</i>
  <i> But he's not here tonight ¶</i>

49:10.715 --> 49:13.482
 <i> ¶ So I walked up to the bar ¶</i>

49:13.484 --> 49:16.652
  <i> ¶ I got a Jager and a shot ¶</i>

49:16.654 --> 49:21.757
     <i> ¶ I drank it down and</i>
    <i> swallowed up my pride ¶</i>

49:24.162 --> 49:25.761
        What can you see?

49:30.768 --> 49:31.734
              Lex?

49:42.780 --> 49:45.548
 <i> ¶ The morning after the club ¶</i>

49:45.550 --> 49:48.551
    <i> ¶ I go out for a walk ¶</i>

49:48.553 --> 49:53.189
      <i> ¶ Turn down a street</i>
     <i> I never took before ¶</i>

49:53.191 --> 49:56.125
        <i> ¶ Lo and behold</i>
       <i> I saw you there ¶</i>

49:56.127 --> 49:58.794
     <i> ¶ You're looking tired</i>
        <i> Worse for wear ¶</i>

49:58.796 --> 50:04.233
      <i> ¶ But I asked you if</i>
    <i> You wanna join for fun ¶</i>

50:04.235 --> 50:06.769
<i>¶ So we walked under the trees ¶</i>

50:06.771 --> 50:09.505
<i>¶ Mixing coffee with some weed ¶</i>

50:09.507 --> 50:14.577
      <i> ¶ Take a sober tone</i>
    <i> And try to settle down ¶</i>

50:14.579 --> 50:20.182
   <i> ¶ We feel the electricity</i>
<i>Through the air of you and me ¶</i>

50:20.184 --> 50:26.055
     <i> ¶ But as you say again</i>
    <i> You've got another guy ¶</i>

50:27.325 --> 50:28.491
           [Dru sighs]

50:30.061 --> 50:32.395
        [metal thudding]

50:32.397 --> 50:33.496
           I can see!

50:34.298 --> 50:35.264
           I can see!

50:36.367 --> 50:37.333
       I, I can feel her!

50:37.335 --> 50:38.401
      She's in my synapses!

50:38.403 --> 50:40.102
 She's, she's in my fingertips!

50:40.838 --> 50:42.238
          [Leo laughs]

50:42.240 --> 50:43.205
              Woo!

50:48.112 --> 50:50.279
    And the crowd goes wild.

50:51.849 --> 50:53.616
        [metal thudding]

50:53.618 --> 50:54.784
          [Leo laughs]

50:54.786 --> 50:56.752
        Oh, stop, please!

50:56.754 --> 50:58.421
 Oh no, no, you're far too kind.

51:01.559 --> 51:02.525
             Woohoo!

51:06.798 --> 51:07.863
        [Lex] Your face.

51:07.865 --> 51:10.332
    Oh, you do make me blush.

51:11.302 --> 51:12.668
         You need help!

51:13.704 --> 51:17.840
   <i> ¶ I don't need anything ¶</i>

51:17.842 --> 51:20.276
          <i> ¶ But you ¶</i>

51:28.319 --> 51:33.422
 [playing "Piano Concerto No 2"
     by Sergei Rachmaninoff]

52:01.752 --> 52:05.621
           -[retching]
          -[splashing]

52:05.623 --> 52:09.558
           [coughing]

52:09.560 --> 52:11.727
        [toilet flushing]

52:14.899 --> 52:17.466
           [sniffling]

52:35.553 --> 52:37.586
           Page, page!

52:40.358 --> 52:41.390
           Fun sponge!

52:42.960 --> 52:43.926
              Sis.

52:55.439 --> 52:57.806
      "As truth and beauty
     shall together thrive,

52:57.808 --> 53:03.179
    If from thyself to store
      thou wouldst convert.

53:03.181 --> 53:07.983
         Or else of thee
      this I prognosticate.

53:07.985 --> 53:11.887
       Thy end is truth's
  and beauty's doom and date."

53:29.540 --> 53:30.606
          Shakespeare.

53:32.977 --> 53:34.577
       Daisy's a big fan.

53:36.614 --> 53:38.347
          [Lex grunts]

53:41.719 --> 53:43.686
     I fed her his completed
  works for language analysis,

53:43.688 --> 53:47.323
   along with 20,000 gigabytes
 of other digitized literature.

53:47.325 --> 53:49.458
  Notably she categorized Romeo
  and Juliet with the comedies

53:49.460 --> 53:51.293
         and recognized
 homoerotic and Catholic trends

53:51.295 --> 53:52.528
     in much of his writing.

53:52.530 --> 53:56.999
    Of course academics have
 pointed out these connections,

53:57.001 --> 53:58.901
     -but I thought it was--
           -[slapping]

53:58.903 --> 54:00.636
        Not my good side.

54:00.638 --> 54:03.672
         -[Lex] Shut up!
  -Have you prayed for me, sis?

54:03.674 --> 54:05.708
That I'll be swept to salvation?

54:18.389 --> 54:21.257
         [ominous music]

54:47.418 --> 54:48.384
           [splashing]

54:48.386 --> 54:49.485
          Hey, hey, aw!

54:50.921 --> 54:51.954
       No, no, no, no, no!

54:51.956 --> 54:54.490
           [trickling]

54:56.027 --> 54:57.293
         You're welcome.

54:59.997 --> 55:02.831
         [drain sucking]

55:03.701 --> 55:05.968
            [hissing]

55:06.771 --> 55:09.438
       [foreboding music]

55:21.385 --> 55:26.088
     -[Leo and Dru coughing]
         -[air hissing]

55:26.090 --> 55:27.389
  The airflow must be oxidized

55:27.391 --> 55:29.725
   by whatever's in that pipe.

55:32.029 --> 55:36.398
     [Dru and Leo coughing]

55:36.400 --> 55:37.966
        Plastics tend to
      be resistant to acid.

55:42.340 --> 55:43.405
              What?

55:47.511 --> 55:50.946
  Okay, okay, okay! Easy! Easy!

55:52.550 --> 55:55.117
          [splattering]

55:56.921 --> 55:59.154
   [Lex] Oh, come on, come on.

55:59.156 --> 56:00.522
           [knocking]

56:00.524 --> 56:01.824
         Coming, coming!

56:24.115 --> 56:27.149
       [soft piano music]

56:45.770 --> 56:46.735
           [growling]

56:46.737 --> 56:48.137
           Tinkerbell?

56:48.139 --> 56:50.606
           [growling]

56:53.477 --> 56:54.676
              Lex?

56:54.678 --> 56:57.780
       [suspenseful music]

56:59.950 --> 57:01.683
           [grunting]

57:09.560 --> 57:11.660
       -[Tinkerbell roars]
              -Run.

57:11.662 --> 57:15.030
          [piano music]

57:16.801 --> 57:19.468
       -[Tinkerbell roars]
           -[Lex] Leo!

57:19.470 --> 57:21.537
          [Leo screams]

57:25.476 --> 57:27.709
       [Tinkerbell growls]

57:29.513 --> 57:32.080
           -[thudding]
     -[Tinkerbell grunting]

57:33.984 --> 57:37.586
    [Leo] Get out of the way,
       get out of the way!
    Get out of the way, move!

57:38.589 --> 57:42.024
        -[liquid hissing]
      -[Tinkerbell howling]

57:50.234 --> 57:52.167
        Three, two, one!

57:52.169 --> 57:55.237
           -[grunting]
           -[creaking]

58:10.521 --> 58:11.787
              Hey.

58:12.590 --> 58:13.822
          What is this?

58:13.824 --> 58:14.857
        A trial version.

58:16.861 --> 58:18.093
      You missed my speech.

58:19.296 --> 58:21.530
  I gave them out at the party.

58:31.976 --> 58:33.308
            How many?

58:47.258 --> 58:49.224
         Say something.

58:49.226 --> 58:51.260
      It was an experiment.

58:54.532 --> 58:55.797
          [Leo grunts]

